                        "name": "9.B.3 Sold production of industry per capita",
                      
                        "goal": "Goal 9. Industry, innovation and infrastructure",
                      
                        "priority": "Strong and intelligent economy strengthening the competitiveness of the region (Strengthening the mechanisms of innovation transfer in the economy and development of intelligent specializations)",
                      
                        "definition": "The value of sales of products (goods and services) of industrial enterprises' own production, divided by the number of inhabitants.",
                      
                        "unit": "PLN",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "Sold industrial production is the basic measure of economic activity (i.e. industrial, construction and assembly, transport and other activities) of industrial enterprises and companies, i.e. economic entities classified according to PKD2007 to sections B, C, D, E.Sold industrial production is the value expressed in current basic prices, i.e. excluding the goods and services tax (VAT), excise tax, and including the value of received subsidies for products (goods and services).",
                      
